lumRoutingMIB.description: The Luminous System MIB contains information related to the Luminous system configurations and monitoring.

lumRouteCfgDownloadHost.name: lumRouteCfgDownloadHost
lumRouteCfgDownloadHost.description: The IP address or name of the Routing configuration file downloading host.

lumRouteCfgDownloadUsrName.name: lumRouteCfgDownloadUsrName
lumRouteCfgDownloadUsrName.description: The user logging name for accessing the routing config file downloading host.

lumRouteCfgDownloadPasswd.name: lumRouteCfgDownloadPasswd
lumRouteCfgDownloadPasswd.description: The password associated with the lumRouteCfgDownloadUsrName when accessing the routing config file downloading host.

lumRouteCfgDownloadPath.name: lumRouteCfgDownloadPath
lumRouteCfgDownloadPath.description: The routing config file name and its directory path on the downloading host.

lumRouteCfgDownloadTimeOut.name: lumRouteCfgDownloadTimeOut
lumRouteCfgDownloadTimeOut.description: The length of time, in minutes, that agent allows the download process to continue.

lumRouteCfgDownloadCmd.name: lumRouteCfgDownloadCmd
lumRouteCfgDownloadCmd.description: Set object to download(2) to active the routing config file download process. The image downloading related objects should have been properly configuered. The download command will be rejected if the the lumRouteCfgDownloadStatus has a value of download-in-progress(2).

lumRouteCfgDownloadStatus.name: lumRouteCfgDownloadStatus
lumRouteCfgDownloadStatus.description: The status of a previously issued routing config file download command.
